{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6af5f499-4aa0-4e14-95e0-ed48e671604b","content":"You can download `dotnet-trace` as a **standalone executable** — no SDK needed.\n\n**Inside the container, run:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -sSL https://aka.ms/dotnet-trace/linux-x64 -o /tmp/dotnet-trace\nchmod +x /tmp/dotnet-trace\n```\n\n**Then collect a CPU trace:**\n\n```bash\n# Find your app's PID\n/tmp/dotnet-trace ps\n\n# Collect with the cpu-sampling profile\n/tmp/dotnet-trace collect -p <PID> --profile cpu-sampling -o /tmp/trace.nettrace\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Use `linux-arm64` instead of `linux-x64` if you're on ARM.\n- The resulting `.nettrace` file can be analyzed with **Visual Studio**, **PerfView**, or **Speedscope** (`--format speedscope`).\n- To copy the trace out: `docker cp <container>:/tmp/trace.nettrace .`\n- If the container also lacks `curl`, you can `docker cp` the binary in from the host instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0a838f22-df11-4521-8c90-00b085803418","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to get `dotnet-trace` into a Linux container that doesn't have the .NET SDK installed, to collect a CPU trace from a .NET 8 app experiencing high CPU.\n\nThis is a knowledge question about .NET diagnostics tooling. I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.\n\nKey points:\n1. `dotnet-trace` is a .NET global tool, but you can also get it as a standalone download (no SDK required).\n2. For containers without the SDK, you can download the standalone version directly.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":415,"requestId":"D848:2A55B4:851770:996D37:69FBEAFC"},"id":"33628047-abde-4a9a-b014-8537a25a63f4","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:29:47.515Z","parentId":"12371e59-d043-4ffc-83d3-fdc49a3abad0"}
